HEADWORD: Pennywort
<hw>Pen"ny*wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A European trailing herb (<spn>Linaria Cymbalaria</spn>) with
roundish, reniform leaves. It is often cultivated in hanging
baskets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>March pennywort</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>Water pennywort</b></col></mcol>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
under <er>March</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pennyworth</ent>⟦br⟧
